content:
A new error started popping up tonight. I don't think it's due to anything I changed. Is it possibly due to the tx server upgrade? I'm get TONS of these:

-tx: Terminology Server: $validate null#shr-oncology-TumorDimensions-model: "null" for Include All codes from http://hl7.org/fhir/data-types, Include All codes from http://hl7.org/fhir/resource-types

Seems only to happen with models... but the tail end of the message ("null" for Include All codes from http://hl7.org/fhir/data-types, Include All codes from http://hl7.org/fhir/resource-types) is always the same.

Doesn't show up in the qa.html, nor does it seem to have any affect on the IG that is produced (as far as I can tell).
it's a notice to me that the terminology server is being used. if it appears more than once across runs, then I have a bug somewhere in the terminology caching logic
you'll got lots (potentially 1000s) of these the first time you run with the new caching set up
If the message is going to stay long-term, you might consider re-wording it so it's more obvious that it's really just reporting a cache miss.
